# oxide rpmbuild tree — check in the build SYSTEM, ignore generated ARTIFACTS.
#
# Checked in (source of truth):
#   SPECS/*.spec            generated recipes (reviewable; rpmbuild input)
#   vendorctl/ (src etc.)   the orchestrator
#   lib/                    shared build glue
#   .rpmmacros-oxide        topdir + dist + signing macros
#   register-*.sh           catalog source: repopulate catalog.db (until export/import
#                           round-trips the orchestration columns — see README TODO)
#   RPMS/RPM-GPG-KEY-oxide   public signing key (consumers import this)
#   README.md

# --- rpmbuild scratch (regenerated every build) ---
/BUILD/
/BUILDROOT/

# --- built artifacts (published to the repo store, not git) ---
/RPMS/**/*.rpm
/SRPMS/
# createrepo_c output + temp
/RPMS/**/repodata/
/RPMS/**/.repodata/

# --- large upstream sources (regenerate via `vendorctl src stage <pkg>`) ---
/SOURCES/*.tar.*
/SOURCES/*.tgz
/SOURCES/*.zip

# --- sqlite runtime (regenerate from catalog.json) ---
/catalog.db
/catalog.db-shm
/catalog.db-wal

# --- rust build dir ---
/vendorctl/target/

# editor / os cruft
*.swp
*~
.DS_Store
